<section class="section">
  <p class="small muted"><a href="/brothers/">← Back to Brothers</a></p>
  <h2>OUR BROTHERS</h2>
  <div class="line"></div>
  <p class="lede">Approximately seventy-two Brothers serve in the Thailand Province, organised across nineteen communities, formation houses, and apostolic works. Together they form one Religious family under the Provincial Superior.</p>

  <blockquote class="callout">
    Out of pastoral discretion, the Brothers' birth dates are not published. Where appropriate, the year of perpetual profession is shown to mark the depth of religious commitment.
  </blockquote>

  <h3 style="margin-top:36px">BROTHERS OF THE PROVINCE</h3>
  <div class="line"></div>
  <p>A complete list of the Brothers presently serving, with their community assignment and year of perpetual profession, is being prepared in collaboration with the Provincial Secretariat. It will appear here once verified against the latest annual <a href="transfers.html">Letter of Obedience</a>.</p>

  <p class="small muted" style="margin-top:24px">For the Brothers serving as Provincial Superior, Councillors, and Bursar, see <a href="/leadership/">Leadership</a>. For the communities where the Brothers live and pray together, see <a href="houses.html">Communities</a>.</p>
</section>

